  "question_id" : 5600668,
  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5600668/how-can-i-initialize-an-arraylist-with-all-zeroes-in-java",
  "title" : "How can I initialize an ArrayList with all zeroes in Java?",
  "body" : "<p>It looks like <code>arraylist</code> is not doing its job for presizing:</p>\n\n<pre><code>// presizing \n\nArrayList&lt;Integer&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;Integer&gt;(60);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Afterwards when I try to access it:</p>\n\n<pre><code>list.get(5) \n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Instead of returning 0 it throws <em>IndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 5 out of bounds for length 0</em>.</p>\n\n<p>Is there a way to initialize all elements to 0 of an exact size like what C++ does?</p>\n"
}